details.name: Australian Grand Prix
details.text: The Australian Grand Prix is an annual motor racing event which is under contract to host Formula One until 2025.

details.name: Lewis Hamilton
details.text: Sir Lewis Carl Davidson Hamilton  (born 7 January 1985) is a British racing driver currently competing in Formula One for Mercedes.

details.name: Charles Leclerc
details.text: Charles Marc Hervé Perceval Leclerc (French pronunciation: ​[ʃaʁl ləklɛʁ]; born 16 October 1997) is a Monégasque racing driver, currently racing in Formula One for Scuderia Ferrari.

details.name: Max Verstappen
details.text: Max Emilian Verstappen (born 30 September 1997) is a Belgian-Dutch racing driver and the 2021 Formula One World Champion.

details.name: Scuderia Ferrari
details.text: Scuderia Ferrari S.p.A. (Italian: [skudeˈriːa ferˈraːri]) is the racing division of luxury Italian auto manufacturer Ferrari and the racing team that competes in Formula One racing.

details.name: Nicholas Latifi
details.text: Nicholas Daniel Latifi (born 29 June 1995) is a Canadian-Iranian racing driver competing for Williams Racing under the Canadian flag in the 2022 Formula One World Championship.

details.name: Fernando Alonso
details.text: Fernando Alonso Díaz (Spanish pronunciation: [feɾˈnando aˈlonso ˈði.aθ] (listen); born 29 July 1981) is a Spanish racing driver currently competing for Alpine in Formula One.

details.name: Red Bull Racing
details.text: Red Bull Racing, also simply known as Red Bull or RBR and competing as Oracle Red Bull Racing, is a Formula One racing team, racing under an Austrian licence and based in the United Kingdom.

details.name: Daniel Ricciardo
details.text: Daniel Joseph Ricciardo  ( "Ricardo"; born 1 July 1989) is an Italian-Australian racing driver who is currently competing in the 2022 FIA Formula One World Drivers Championship driving for the McLaren Formula One team, under the Australian flag.

competing_in: 2022 fia formula one world drivers championship

details.name: David Schumacher (racing driver)
details.text: David Schumacher (born 23 October 2001) is a German racing driver, son of former Formula One driver Ralf Schumacher, nephew of seven-time Formula One world champion Michael Schumacher, and cousin of current Formula One driver Mick Schumacher.

details.name: Niki Lauda
details.text: Andreas Nikolaus "Niki" Lauda (22 February 1949 – 20 May 2019) was an Austrian Formula One driver and aviation entrepreneur.

details.name: Sebastian Vettel
details.text: Sebastian Vettel (German pronunciation: [zeˈbasti̯a(ː)n ˈfɛtl̩] (listen); born 3 July 1987) is a German racing driver who competes in Formula One for Aston Martin, having previously driven for BMW Sauber, Toro Rosso, Red Bull, and Ferrari.

details.name: Rubens Barrichello
details.text: Rubens "Rubinho" Gonçalves Barrichello (Portuguese pronunciation: [ˈʁubẽjz ɡõ'sawviz baʁiˈkɛlʊ], [ʁuˈbĩjʊ]; born 23 May 1972) is a Brazilian racing driver who competed in Formula One between 1993 and 2011.

details.name: McLaren Group
details.text: The McLaren Group is a British company based in Woking, England, which is involved in Formula One and other motorsport and the manufacture of luxury cars.The group was founded by Ron Dennis shortly after his acquisition of the McLaren Formula One team in 1981, as the TAG McLaren Group due to a partnership with Mansour Ojjeh's TAG Group.

details.name: Martin Brundle
details.text: Martin John Brundle (born 1 June 1959) is a British former racing driver, best known as a Formula One driver and as a commentator for ITV Sport from 1997 to 2008, the BBC from 2009 to 2011, and Sky Sports since 2012.Brundle contested the 1983 British Formula Three Championship, finishing a close second to Ayrton Senna, and the two progressed to Formula One the next year.

details.name: David Coulthard
details.text: David Marshall Coulthard  (; born 27 March 1971) is a British former racing driver from Scotland, later turned presenter, commentator and journalist.

details.name: Jenson Button
details.text: Jenson Alexander Lyons Button  (born 19 January 1980) is a British racing driver.

details.name: Kimi Räikkönen
details.text: Kimi-Matias Räikkönen (Finnish pronunciation: [ˈkimi ˈmɑtiɑs ˈræi̯kːønen]; born 17 October 1979), nicknamed "The Iceman", is a Finnish racing driver who competed in Formula One between 2001 and 2021 for Sauber, McLaren, Ferrari, Lotus, and Alfa Romeo.

details.name: Nigel Mansell
details.text: Nigel Ernest James Mansell,  (; born 8 August 1953) is a British former racing driver who won both the Formula One World Championship (1992) and the CART Indy Car World Series (1993).

details.name: Mick Schumacher
details.text: Mick Schumacher (German pronunciation: [ˈmɪk ˈʃuːmaxɐ]; born 22 March 1999) is a Swiss-born German racing driver.

details.name: Michael Schumacher
details.text: Michael Schumacher (; German: [ˈmɪçaːʔeːl ˈʃuːmaxɐ] (listen); born 3 January 1969) is a German former racing driver who competed in Formula One for Jordan, Benetton, Ferrari, and Mercedes.

details.name: Juan Pablo Montoya
details.text: Juan Pablo Montoya Roldán (Spanish pronunciation: [ˈxwan ˈpaβlo monˈtoʝa rolˈdan]; born September 20, 1975), is a Colombian racing driver.

details.name: Nico Hülkenberg
details.text: Nicolas Hülkenberg (German pronunciation: [ˈniːko ˈhʏlkənbɛɐ̯k], born 19 August 1987) is a German professional racing driver who currently serves as the reserve driver in Formula One for the Aston Martin F1 Team.

details.name: Mika Häkkinen
details.text: Mika Pauli Häkkinen (Finnish: [ˈmikɑ ˈhækːinen] (listen); born 28 September 1968), nicknamed "The Flying Finn", is a Finnish former racing driver.

details.name: Robert Kubica
details.text: Robert Józef Kubica (Polish pronunciation: [ˈrɔbɛrt kuˈbit͡sa] (listen); born 7 December 1984) is a Polish racing driver.

details.name: Sergio Pérez
details.text: Sergio Michel Pérez Mendoza (Spanish: [ˈseɾxjo ˈpeɾes] (listen); born 26 January 1990), nicknamed "Checo", is a Mexican racing driver who races in Formula One for Red Bull Racing, having previously driven for Sauber, McLaren, Force India, and Racing Point.

details.name: Nico Rosberg
details.text: Nico Erik Rosberg (born 27 June 1985) is a German-Finnish former racing driver.

details.name: Damon Hill
details.text: Damon Graham Devereux Hill,  (born 17 September 1960) is a British former racing driver from England and the 1996 Formula One World Champion.

details.name: Eddie Irvine
details.text: Edmund Irvine Jr. (; born 10 November 1965) is a former racing driver from Northern Ireland.

details.name: Yuki Tsunoda
details.text: Yuki Tsunoda (Japanese: 角田 裕毅, Tsunoda Yūki; born 11 May 2000) is a Japanese racing driver who is racing for Scuderia AlphaTauri in Formula One.

details.name: Antonio Giovinazzi
details.text: Antonio Maria Giovinazzi (Italian pronunciation: [anˈtɔːnjo dʒoviˈnattsi]; born 14 December 1993) is an Italian racing driver who is currently racing for Dragon/Penske Autosport in Formula E. He was the 2015 FIA Formula 3 European Championship runner-up and raced with Prema in the 2016 GP2 Series, again finishing runner-up with five wins and eight overall podiums.

details.name: Felipe Massa
details.text: Felipe Massa (Portuguese pronunciation: [fiˈlipi ˈmasɐ], born 25 April 1981) is a Brazilian racing driver.

details.name: Mario Andretti

details.name: Lando Norris
details.text: Lando Norris (; born 13 November 1999) is a British-Belgian racing driver currently competing in Formula One with McLaren, racing under the British flag.

details.name: René Arnoux
details.text: René Alexandre Arnoux (born 4 July 1948) is a French former racing driver who competed in 12 Formula One seasons (1978 to 1989).

details.name: Heikki Kovalainen
details.text: Heikki Johannes Kovalainen (Finnish pronunciation: [ˈhei̯kːi ˈkoʋɑlɑi̯nen]; born 19 October 1981) is a Finnish racing driver.

details.name: Emerson Fittipaldi
details.text: Emerson Wojciechowska Fittipaldi (Portuguese pronunciation: [ˈɛmeʁsõ fitʃiˈpawdʒi]; born 12 December 1946) is a retired Brazilian automobile racing driver who won both the Formula One World Championship and the Indianapolis 500 twice each and the CART championship once.

details.name: Jacky Ickx
details.text: Jacques Bernard "Jacky" Ickx (French pronunciation: ​[ʒaki ɪks]; born 1 January 1945) is a Belgian former racing driver who won the 24 Hours of Le Mans six times (second-highest of all time) and achieved eight wins and 25 podium finishes in Formula One.

details.name: Nick Heidfeld

details.name: Patrick Tambay

details.name: Oliver Bearman

details.name: Jochen Mass
details.text: Jochen Richard Mass (born 30 September 1946) is a German former racing driver.

details.name: Pierre Gasly

details.name: Ralf Schumacher
details.text: Ralf Schumacher (born 30 June 1975) is a German former racing driver.

details.name: Alain Prost

details.name: Brendon Hartley

details.name: Jean Alesi

details.name: Jacques Villeneuve
details.text: Jacques Joseph Charles Villeneuve  (French: [ʒɑk vilnœv] born 9 April 1971) is a Canadian professional racing driver and amateur musician who won the 1997 Formula One World Championship with Williams.

details.name: Jody Scheckter

details.name: Antonio Fuoco

details.name: Dino Beganovic
details.text: Dino Beganovic (Bosnian: Beganović [ˈdino bɛˈɡanovitɕ]; born January 19, 2004) is a Swedish-Bosnian racing driver, currently competing in the Formula Regional European Championship for Prema Powerteam.

details.name: Nelson Piquet

details.name: Keke Rosberg
details.text: Keijo Erik Rosberg (born 6 December 1948), known as "Keke" (Finnish pronunciation: [ˈkeke ˈruːsbæri] (listen)), is a Finnish former racing driver and winner of the 1982 Formula One World Championship.

details.name: Valtteri Bottas
details.text: Valtteri Viktor Bottas (Finnish pronunciation: [ˈʋɑltːeɾi ˈbotːɑs]; born 28 August 1989) is a Finnish racing driver currently competing in Formula One for Alfa Romeo, having previously driven for Mercedes from 2017 to 2021 and Williams from 2013 to 2016.

details.name: Arthur Leclerc
details.text: Arthur Leclerc (born 14 October 2000) is a Monégasque racing driver.

details.name: McLaren
details.text: McLaren Racing Limited is a British motor racing team based at the McLaren Technology Centre in Woking, Surrey, England.

details.name: Haas F1 Team
